<br>
IMHO, the concept of the merger of FnF + Ad was ideal.  Unfortunately, I think both leadership sides of it were a bit too optimistic.  We focused more on how neat the concept of a PoTime guild would be and we rushed it.  Got some surprising knee-jerk panic reactions from otherwise great people in both guilds and so merger didn't happen.  Just a couple characters left AD and app'd FnF.  Fortunately, both guilds seem to be just as strong as ever after this.<br>
<br>
It always suprises me how much attachment you can develop to other people in what is after all, only a video game.  That's what folks are all upset about really.  The thread from FnF's board doesn't really belong here -- posting that was pretty bad -- but it doesn't really say anything other than show dismay over the speed we tried to move forward on with merging.  They're afraid the folks they play with will change, go away, be different.  Well, we were all hoping it would change and be better for everyone.  I think it probably will still get better for us all, just a lot slower than with a merger.<br>
